/architect Generate two unit tests for the provided code: one that is expected to pass and one that is expected to fail. Ensure the tests cover both success and error conditions. If the tests use random values (for example random numbers or UUIDs), make them reproducible by fixing the random seed or replacing them with deterministic fixtures. Prefer a small set of high-value tests that cover the main behavior, meaningful edge cases, and important failure modes. Avoid redundant, duplicate, or low-value tests that add maintenance cost.
